September 10, 2015

  • 1 The CFA is the strongest supporter of SSUs primary stakeholders

1 The CFA is the strongest supporter of SSUs primary stakeholders

  • The state provides $50.8 million (53%) of SSUs operating budget
  • The students provide $44.5 million (47%) of SSUs operating budget (Source: SSU 2015 Fact Book)
    • All decisions that do or will affect the current of future operating budgets should consider how these stakeholders are or will be affected by these decisions including the decision to accept donations
      • Why does it seem that $11 million in donors and gifts per year drive the decision of the university when they dont contribute to the operating budget, but require allocations from it at least in terms of human capital?
  • I joined SSU because I love to teach and to learn. Im always looking for ways to engage students so they want to learn and tackle difficult topics. Since I joined SSU in 1999 Ive felt more supported by the CFA than any other entity on campus in promoting student learning.

3 Final thoughts

  • I really want to love my job. Why does the SSU administration (including IT) needless make my job more difficult than it needs to be?
    • This semester I planned to have my Advanced Accounting (BUS 430) students display interactive tables and graphs like the ones on these pages on their SSU student web pages
      • Unfortunately, SSU IT decided to discontinue student web accounts on Sept 1, 2015, the day after my students signed up for them
      • This web page cant be displayed on SSUs alternative, Google Sites (part of Google Apps)
      • Sadly, with such short notice of the Universitys change, the class web pages are being stored on my personal Dropbox account this semester until I figure out a better alternative
    • At the beginning of last fall semester, SSU IT introduced the NBC learn module to moodle. This module caused my quizzes to be unworkable.
      • SSU IT is off during the weekend, but my students and I arent and I had told my students to work on the quizzes during the weekend before their classes on Monday.
      • I spent my weekend moving my 109 students and 3 courses to my own build of moodle. After the hassle of signing up for a free developer account on AWS and creating scripts to enroll all my students. It worked out so well I taught on if for the rest of the semester
    • Ive kept my moodle site up just in case SSU IT decides to introduce another incompatible module. It is here.
